    <fig id="fig1">
      <label>Fig.&#xA0;1</label>
      <caption>
        <p>Conceptual overview of our compositing setup. A layer definition is comprised of the layer content in form of an <mml:math id="M29" altimg="si0001.gif" overflow="scroll"><mml:mi>rgb</mml:mi><mml:mi>&#x3B1;</mml:mi><mml:mi mathvariant="normal">z</mml:mi></mml:math> image, an additional layer mask, and an associated blending operator. Layers are arranged in a hierarchical blending tree as exemplified in the figure: the upper highlighted layer in the stack consists of three sublayers and the lower highlighted layer consists of five sublayers one of which is itself composed of two sublayers.</p>
      </caption>
